<p>I'm writing a code to swap integers in an array and I want to know how I can exit a loop without using a break statement and keeping my logic consistent. Here is my code below: </p>  <pre><code>int swapped = 0; if (arrays[0][first] % 2 == 0) {      cout &lt;&lt; arrays[0][first] &lt;&lt; " is odd " &lt;&lt; endl;      for (int i = 1; i &lt; arraycount; ++i)      {          for (int j = 1; j &lt; arrays[i][0] + 1; ++j)          {              if (arrays[i][j] % 2 != 0)              {                   int temp = arrays[i][j];                   cout &lt;&lt; "Array #" &lt;&lt; 1 &lt;&lt; " value " &lt;&lt; arrays[0][first] &lt;&lt; " swapped with "                           &lt;&lt; "Array #" &lt;&lt; i &lt;&lt; " value " &lt;&lt; temp;                    arrays[i][j] = arrays[0][first];                   arrays[0][first] = temp;                   swapped = 1;                   break;               }           }           if (swapped) {                 break;           } </code></pre>